All done. Here's a summary of what was implemented:

**Files created:**
- `src/types.ts` - TypeScript type definitions
- `src/claim-office.ts` - Core business logic (`computeQuote`, `processClaim`, `createPolicy`)
- `src/claim-office.spec.ts` - 34 tests covering all rules
- `src/cli.ts` - CLI entry point reading JSON from stdin, writing JSON to stdout
- `src/cli-runner.mjs` - Node.js runner wrapper
- `claim-office` - Shell wrapper script for the CLI

**Key implementation decisions:**
- Policy-wide modifiers (loyalty, first insurance, follow-up) apply to the **raw policy base** (sum of item base premiums without surcharges)
- Item-specific surcharges (cursed 50%, enchantment ≥5 30%) are calculated on individual item base premiums
- First insurance surcharge **always** applies; follow-up discount also applies when `isFirstContract=false`
- Component block-of-3 discount (60 G vs 75 G) only applies when **exactly** 3 of the same type
- High-enchantment (≥8) clause wins over dragon-material for payouts (50% then deductible)
- Premiums round up (ceiling), payouts round down (floor)
- All 34 tests pass
